For a general suggestion, I recommend you to look at the below link to learn how to install packages in your conda environment. (https://stackoverflow.com/questions/41060382/using-pip-to-install-packages-to-anaconda-environment)

Quick summary, use your conda environment's pip path to download packages (e.g Dont use "pip install PACKAGE", rather use "/anaconda/envs/YOUR_CONDAENV_NAME/bin/pip install PACKAGE"). You can see the explanation thread below. When you use "pip" directly, it downloads to base environment and hence can produce conflicts.


